sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as Consuming app
    participant Signing as AppSigningBackend
    participant Backend as Selected signer backend
    participant HSM as Secure Enclave / TPM / software fallback
    participant Metadata as key metadata and cached public key
    participant Target as Target protocol\nSSH agent / git signing / helper

    App->>Signing: create signing backend(StorageConfig)
    Signing->>Backend: ensure signing key exists
    Backend->>HSM: create or load P-256 signing key
    Backend->>Metadata: save/load .meta and .pub artifacts
    Backend-->>Signing: signer ready

    Target->>App: signing request
    App->>Signing: sign(label, message)
    Signing->>Backend: sign with requested AccessPolicy
    Backend->>HSM: ECDSA P-256 SHA-256 signing operation
    HSM-->>Backend: signature
    Backend-->>Signing: DER signature
    Signing-->>App: signature
    App-->>Target: protocol-specific response

    Note over Backend,HSM: Hardware-backed paths keep the private key non-exportable.

